{
  "text": "Simultaneously, the water deficit can promote changes in the capacity of the nitrogen fixation in Consequences of the water deficit on water relations and symbiosis in Vigna unguiculata cultivars legumes, due to the smaller water absorption and consequent reduction in the water supplement in tissues, in which it might promote damage in the nitrogen compound translocation. This way, it inhibits the biochemical activity responsible by the nitrogen metabolism [CITATION_1] .",
